gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 121, Raptors 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Raptors, 121-111. Tobias Harris recorded a season-high 33 points, along with eight rebounds and seven assists for the 76ers, with Tyrese Maxey (33 points, 10 assists) and Joel Embiid (31 points, 10 rebounds) combining for 64 points in the victory. Pascal Siakam tallied 31 points, five rebounds, and five assists for the Raptors in the losing effort. The 76ers improve to 20-8 in the regular season, while the Raptors fall to 11-17.
